description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Reference Number: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job title: Screening and Immunisation Coordinator &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employer: &lt;/strong&gt;Public Health England&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;PHE East of England, East Anglia Screening and Immunisation &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations: Fulbourn, Cambridge&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Number of posts: 1 x 0.8wte post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;AfC Band 7 £38,890 -£44,503 / Pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CS SEO Outer £38,202– £44,240 / Pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:&lt;/strong&gt; 30 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type&lt;/strong&gt; Fixed Term Contract 1 Year&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 8th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: Week commencing 16th November&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Public Health England provides strategic leadership and vision for protecting and improving the nation’s health. Its ambition is to lead nationally and enable locally, a transformation in the health expectations of all people in England regardless of where they live and the circumstance of their birth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Screening and immunisation team are looking to recruit a Screening and Immunisation Coordinator based in Fulbourn Cambridge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Screening and Immunisation Coordinator (SIC) plays a key role in supporting the commissioning and delivery of consistently resilient, high quality national screening and immunisation programmes within the East region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, energetic, motivated team player, with an excellent knowledge base and ideally someone with a screening or immunisations background. We would particularly be interested to hear from applicants with experience in antenatal and newborn screening.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of an established team with a valuable role in coordinating and shaping the delivery of these services and reducing health inequalities. You will provide direct support to a Screening and Immunisation Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team would like the practitioner to be experienced, passionate about immunisation and screening, energetic and motivated but also someone who would want to add value to the team by being supportive and flexible with a desire to deliver to a high standard. The individual will need to have the ability to build strong, collaborative working relationships with key stakeholders; this will necessitate travelling within Cambridgeshire, Peterborough, Norfolk and Suffolk when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the work in the screening and immunization the successful candidate will be expected to support the PHE COVID-19 response when required in the Coronavirus Response Cell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car driver and access to a car is essential for this role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return the team will support with workload and any developmental needs, to make the post a success for the individual and the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are strongly advised to use the criteria in the person specification (available online) as sub-headings in their application to make it clear how they meet each of the selection criteria. Please also see the job description for competencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Public Health England promotes diversity in the workplace and is an equal opportunities employer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Option 3 – External&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open to all external applicants (anyone) from outside the Civil Service (including by definition internal applicants).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or an informal discussion about the post, please contact Tina ten Hove: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;tina.tenhove@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; or telephone: 07920 251613&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
